git init                         --- THIS COMMAND WILL INSTALL THE GIT FOLDER IN YOUR 
git add README.md                --- THIS WILL ADD A README FILE TO YOUR FOLDER
git add .     (GIT ADD ALL)      --- THIS WILL ADD ALL SAVED THE FILE READY TO UPLOAD . 
git commit -m "first commit"     --- THIS WILL CREATE A CHECK POINT FOR YOUR FILES IN REPO (GIT COMMIT --> CREATES CHECKPOINT --> -m "message" )
git branch -M main               ---this willl create a main/MASTER branch which will be your master or a production
git remote add origin https://github.com/SourceCode-code/Source_and_code_batch_5.git --> this give the location of the main repo to connect with this folder
git push -u origin main         --- this commands will finally show all your all your files to github


THIS ABOVE WILL ONLY BE DONE ONCE --> WHEN FIRST UPLOADING FILES TO REPO

IF I HAVE TO SEND THE UPDATED CHANGES IN THE REPO SO NOW I HAVE ENTER 3 COMMANDS 

// 1  git add .   ---> makes all updated files ready for upload in the repo
// 2  git commit -m "message" --> created a checkout with message 
